    <LessonRevisionNumber>268</LessonRevisionNumber>
    <LessonDescription/>
    <opTopTitle>Self-Care</opTopTitle>
    <opTopContent>&lt;p&gt;Self-care refers to activities and practices that we can engage in on a regular basis to reduce stress and maintain and enhance our short- and longer-term health and well-being. Self-care is necessary for your effectiveness and success in honoring your professional and personal commitments. Self-care is not simply about limiting or addressing professional stressors. It is also about enhancing your overall well-being.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning Objectives:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8226; Summarize the value of self-care in one's life&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8226; Manage time for self-care&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8226; Identify elements for physical, emotional, and spiritual self-care&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8226; Create a self-care plan for personal use&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8226; List top three things physical, emotional and spiritual self-care that worked for you&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8226; Provide rationale for selecting particular self-care solutions&lt;/p&gt;</opTopContent>
